sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser
    participant Edge as CDN Edge<br/>TLS Termination
    participant Origin as Origin Server

    Note over Browser,Origin: Mode 1: Full (Strict) - Best Security

    Browser->>Edge: ClientHello (TLS 1.3)
    Edge-->>Browser: ServerHello + CDN Certificate<br/>(issued by Let's Encrypt or DigiCert)
    Browser->>Edge: Finished (encrypted tunnel established)
    Note over Browser,Edge: HTTPS connection to CDN

    Edge->>Origin: ClientHello (TLS 1.2/1.3)
    Origin-->>Edge: ServerHello + Origin Certificate<br/>(must be valid CA-signed cert)
    Edge->>Edge: Validate origin certificate chain
    Edge->>Origin: Finished
    Note over Edge,Origin: HTTPS connection to origin<br/>Certificate VERIFIED

    Note over Browser,Origin: Mode 2: Flexible - Lowest Security

    Browser->>Edge: TLS 1.3 Handshake
    Edge-->>Browser: CDN Certificate
    Note over Browser,Edge: HTTPS to CDN

    Edge->>Origin: HTTP (plaintext, port 80)
    Note over Edge,Origin: NO encryption to origin<br/>Data exposed between CDN and origin

    Note over Browser,Origin: Mode 3: Keyless SSL - Maximum Control

    Browser->>Edge: ClientHello
    Edge->>Edge: Need private key<br/>for ServerHello signature
    Edge->>Origin: Sign this handshake data<br/>(key server at customer premises)
    Origin->>Origin: Sign with private key<br/>(key never leaves customer HSM)
    Origin-->>Edge: Signed handshake data
    Edge-->>Browser: ServerHello + Certificate<br/>(signed by customer's key)
    Note over Edge: CDN never possesses<br/>the private key
